==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Climactic
<hw>Cli*mac"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to a climax; forming, or of the nature of, a climax, or ascending
series.</def></p>

<p><q>A fourth kind of parallelism . . . is still sufficiently marked to
be noticed by the side of those described by Lowth, viz.,
<qex>climactic</qex> parallelism (sometimes called ⟦ldquo⟧ascending
rhythm⟦rdquo⟧).</q> <rj><qau>S. R. Driver.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Climatal</ent>⟦br⟧
